str2: To exercise oversight, care for, visit. From epi and skopeo; to oversee; by implication, to beware.
Not, lest. A primary particle of qualified negation; not, lest; also (whereas ou expects an affirmative one) whether.

str2: Any one, some one, a certain one or thing. An enclitic indefinite pronoun; some or any person or object.

str2: From husteros; to be later, i.e. to be inferior; generally, to fall short.
From, away from. A primary particle; 'off, ' i.e. Away, in various senses.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
From chairo; graciousness, of manner or act.
A deity, especially the supreme Divinity; figuratively, a magistrate; by Hebraism, very.
Not, lest. A primary particle of qualified negation; not, lest; also (whereas ou expects an affirmative one) whether.
A root, shoot, source; that which comes from the root, a descendent. Apparently a primary word; a 'root'.
Bitterness, harshness, hence met: an embittered (resentful) spirit. From pikros; acridity, literally or figuratively.

str2: To grow, grow up, spring up.
Up, above, up to the top, up to the brim, things above, heaven, the heavenly region. Adverb from anti; upward or on the top.

str2: To disturb, cause tumult, trouble, annoy. From en and ochleo; to crowd in, i.e. to annoy.
